title: Grateful Dead Live at Providence Civic Center on 1979-11-04
lineage: MAC > Nakamichi DR-2 > Edirol FA-66 > Wavelab > CD-Wave > TLH > FLAC 2496
description:
Set 1

Minglewood Blues, They Love Each Other, Me & My Uncle-> Big River, Althea, Easy To Love You, Brown Eyed Women, Lost Sailor-> Saint Of Circumstance-> Deal

Set 2

Alabama Getaway-> Greatest Story Ever Told, Ship of Fools, Estimated Prophet-> He's Gone-> Drums-> The Other One-> Wharf Rat-> Around & Around, E: U.S. Blues

reviews.review_text:
Iranian Hostage Crisis Weird that this was the beginning of the Iranian hostage situation, way back when.
But a great, overlooked in my opinion, second set. New arrival Alabama Getaway/Greatest Story.  Loved the 79 jams out of Estimated with Phil and Brent playing off each other.  Melodicjam into He's Gone.  Scary space into the post-drums Other One of this era, (not just another one)
